Cut the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into very small chunks) in half through the root, peel and chop into very small chunks. Peel and bash the @garlic{2%cloves}. Tip: Keep the garlic relatively whole so you can remove it once it has done its job and released its flavour. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1/2%bunch}. Drain the @mixed beans{2%cups} and rinse well.

Heat a splash of @olive oil{a splash} in a #pan on medium heat. Once warm, gently cook your onion and @dried thyme{1/2%tsp} for ~{3%minutes} until soft. Tip: If the onion begins to colour, add a splash of water and turn the heat down a bit.

Add the @British smoked bacon lardons{2} to your onion along with your garlic and cook for ~{5%minutes}. Tip: You want the pancetta to go ever so slightly crispy at the edges.

Add the @smoked paprika{1.5%tsp}, @chopped tomatoes{2%cans}, mixed beans and a pinch of @?sugar{pinch}. Season with @salt{pinch} and a few good grinds of @black pepper{}. Give it all a good stir and let it bubble gently for ~smoky baked beans{20%minutes} or until it is nice and thick. Once thickened stir through your parsley.

Bring a large #pot of water to a gentle boil with a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Chop the @potato{2} into approximately 3cm cubes (no need to peel!) and add to the pot. Cook for around ~{15%minutes} until soft. Tip: The potato is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through. Drain and mash your potato with a little @?milk{} and @?butter{}(if you have some) and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Preheat your #grill to high. Place the @pork and oregano sausage{8} on a #baking tray (with some foil underneath to save washing up!). Cook under your #grill for ~{15%minutes}, turning occasionally to get a nice even colour.

Slice your sausage at an angle and serve on a mound of your mash potato and a big ladle of your smoky baked beans!